<h1 class="bac"><%=program.Item("title")%></h1>

<div class="expanded">
<% call expandableH2("our_business", true) %>
<div>
<p class="bac">Global Corporate and Investment Banking (GCIB) focuses on building long-term relationships with more than 3,000 large U.S. and multinational corporations, financial institutions and financial sponsors, by providing strong advisory expertise and capitalizing on powerful M &amp;A, corporate banking, treasury, debt and equity product expertise, to deliver integrated financial solutions.</p>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<% call expandableH2("overview", false) %>
<div>
<h3 class="bac">Placement</h3>
<p class="bac">Associates are hired and placed directly with a specific group. Group placement is determined by considering business needs and the interests/skills of the Associate. The groups span across country, industry and product (not all groups exist in all countries):</p>
<h3 class="bac">Country</h3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Hong Kong</li>
	<li>Japan</li>
	<li>Singapore</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="bac">Industry</h3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Consumer and Retail</li>
	<li>Energy and Power</li>
	<li>Financial Institutions</li>
	<li>Healthcare</li>
	<li>Industrials</li>
	<li>Real Estate</li>
	<li>Resources</li>
	<li>Telecom, Media  &amp; Technology</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="bac">Product</h3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Financial Sponsors</li>
	<li>General Execution</li>
	<li>Mergers  &amp; Acquisitions</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="bac">Responsibilities</h3>
<p class="bac">Investment Banking Associates play a key role in the origination and execution of work with key clients and take on many responsibilities, including but not limited to:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Working on deal teams with senior bankers and experts from other areas within the firm</li>
	<li>Conducting sophisticated financial analysis and relevant industry research</li>
	<li>Participating in due diligence sessions</li>
	<li>Assisting with structuring transactions, pricing and distributing securities, and closing deals</li>
	<li>Be involved in developing new businesses, preparing and participating in client presentations, and marketing new products</li>
	<li>Assessing the impact of a transaction on a client&#39;s financial results and capital structure</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<% call expandableH2("qualifications", false) %>
<div>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Final year full time MBA student, graduating in 2012</li>
	<li>Bachelor/master&#39;s degree holder</li>
	<li>Outstanding academic achievement</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="bac">Experience</h3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Between 3-5 years&#39; relevant work experience</li>
	<li>A track record of superior performance in extracurricular and professional activities</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="bac">Skills and abilities</h3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Strong quantitative and analytical skills</li>
	<li>Knowledge of accounting and finance, and strong interest in company financing</li>
	<li>Ability to apply advanced oral and written communication skills to create a positive impression and professional rapport</li>
	<li>Ability to work independently while functioning as part of a team</li>
	<li>Appropriate language capabilities</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="bac">Personal traits</h3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>High degree of professionalism and integrity</li>
	<li>A high degree of initiative and motivation</li>
	<li>Strong attention to detail</li>
	<li>Quick learner and interest in taking on new responsibilities</li>
	<li>Client focused</li>
	<li>Results oriented</li>
	<li>Ability to work well with others</li>
	<li>Ability to maintain composure and confidence while juggling conflicting priorities</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<% call expandableH2("training", false) %>
<div>
<p class="bac">Full-time Associates are hired upon completion of their undergraduate/master&#39;s degree. Your career as an Associate will begin with a formal training program which takes place in New York for all Associates globally, and is considered one of the best in the industry. Instruction is provided by Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America professionals and leading business school professors.</p>
<p class="bac nobr">The training program includes:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>A firm wide orientation program to introduce you to Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America</li>
	<li>An overview of the financial markets and essential business skills</li>
	<li>An intensive training program customized for Associates that prepares you for your placement in Investment Banking by simulating actual work assignments, covering quantitative fundamentals, and preparing you for life as an Associate.</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">After the formal training program, Associates relocate to the Asia Pacific office that hired them and begin working. Training continues on the job and through the online learning network for continuing education as well as relevant classroom training throughout your career.</p>
</div></div>

